 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 01:19:43 -0400

job-scheduler (26.06) mx; urgency=medium

  * Jobs scheduled for both a day of the month and a weekday (for example
    "the 15th or every Friday") now run on either day, matching how cron works
  * Invalid time entries are no longer silently changed; the editor now flags
    the problem and keeps your entry until it is valid
  * The time picker now highlights selected boxes using your system theme, so
    they stay readable in dark mode
  * The list of upcoming run times now scrolls to the selected entry
  * Impossible schedules such as "February 30th" are recognised right away
    instead of briefly freezing the app
  * Reading crontabs no longer shows a false error when the system prints
    harmless warnings, and existing comments are kept more reliably
  * Removed a stray empty column from the jobs list

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:00:00 -0400

